  "title": "Shopping Cart (JS)",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "category": "Class variable + unimplemented method",
  "description": "Given a list of orders, return a dict mapping each customer's name to their order total.\n\nEach order: `{\"customer\": str, \"items\": [[name, price, qty], ...], \"discount\": int}`\n\nA discount of `p` reduces every item's unit price by `p%` before multiplying by quantity.\n\n**Example 1:**\nInput: `[{\"customer\": \"Alice\", \"items\": [[\"shirt\", 20, 1], [\"pants\", 40, 1]], \"discount\": 0}]`\nOutput: `{\"Alice\": 60}`\n\n**Example 2:**\nInput: `[{\"customer\": \"Bob\", \"items\": [[\"hat\", 50, 1]], \"discount\": 10}]`\nOutput: `{\"Bob\": 45.0}`\nExplanation: 50 × (1 − 0.10) = 45.0\n\n**Example 3:**\nInput: `[{\"customer\": \"Carol\", \"items\": [[\"pen\", 5, 2], [\"notebook\", 8, 1]], \"discount\": 0}]`\nOutput: `{\"Carol\": 18}`\n\n**Constraints:**\n- `1 <= len(orders) <= 50`\n- `0 <= discount <= 100`\n- Each customer name is unique in the input.\n\n**Tasks:** Two things need fixing — isolate cart state between customers, and implement `applyDiscount(percent)` in `cart.js`.",
